    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Areas where lacunae, gaps, cracks, pores, holes, or other losses or differences in grade have been filled or leveled with a filling material, such as in paintings, mosaics, frames, sculpture, architectural elements, landscape surfaces, and other objects of many kinds. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Delen van een mosiaïque waarin de oorspronkelijke mozaïekblokjes of mortel ontbreken en de leemten zijn opgevuld met nieuw materiaal, bijvoorbeeld mortel of nieuwe mozaïekblokjes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bereich, in dem es Lacunae, Spalten, Risse, Poren, Löcher oder andere Einbußen oder Unterschiede in der Qualität gibt, die gefüllt oder mit einem Füllmaterial eingeebnet werden, wie zum Beispiel in der Malerei, bei Mosaiken, Rahmen, Skulpturen, Architekturelementen, Landschaftsflächen und vielerlei anderen Objekten.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
